	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just a note on the poisons you were talking about:The root poison is root and 50% slow, the blinding ones are blind and atk debuff. The blind is very effect in pvp, lasts for 72 secs for second tier one. There are also mana draining poisons. With the second tier of this one for my 47 rogue steals 265 mana. Not a lot but helps. Also there is a nasty snare poison, get a 50% snare on the tier 2 one at level 47. Many other very useful poisons. Also in pvp instill doubt works very well for me, many times fearing the opponent several times in one fight. All in all rogues not too bad in pvp in my opinion.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Ubunoa Yandini<br>Knights of Trinity<br>Quellious</td></tr>
